that I live in a small town now, and we don't really have any sort of 'center' or 'scene' for meeting people/hanging out or anything like that. I'm sure there are groups for singles and other age cohorts. I don't know how you'd find out about them unless you picked up a local newspaper (that's one of my goals for this year, by the way, I really want to improve my Spanish skills so that I can read one of those newspapers). I think it depends on where you live. Do you have any gay bars or anything like that? For us, picking up any of the gay papers/magazines in the bars might be an idea.

Good luck!

Hi there!

If you are anywhere near Madrid (and even if you are not! ;) there is a good site for information on social events and groups - http://www.iwannawriteis.wordpress.com

It doesn't specifically talk about dating but it has events for gay groups and singles meet-ups. It's a very nice, positive blog with lots of information :) There is also the web-page for Madrid Gay Pride (although it looks like you'd have to look that up before mid-May for next year) http://www.madridpride.com

Good luck! :)
